name: 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate reductoisomerase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: The enzyme requires Mn2+, Co2+ or Mg2+ for activity, with the first being most effective. The enzyme from several eubacteria, including Escherichia coli, forms part of an alternative nonmevalonate pathway for terpenoid biosynthesis (for diagram, {terp/nonMVA}). The mechanism has been shown to be a retroaldol/aldol reaction [2].

references.title: A 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase catalyzing the formation of 2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 4-phosphate in an alternative nonmevalonate pathway for terpenoid biosynthesis.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 95 (1998) 9879-84.

references.title: A secondary kinetic isotope effect study of the 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate reductoisomerase-catalyzed reaction: evidence for a retroaldol-aldol rearrangement.
